        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 3:49PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 349 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Akron, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Akron, Otis, Platner and Fremont Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Prepare for sudden gusty winds. Secure loose objects and move to a
safe shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
